               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>Enhanced bus driver training is a key component of achieving Vision Zero and recent research has shown that, in particular, this should cover detecting pedestrians, cyclists and motorcyclists, anticipating other road users’ behaviour and hazard perception training. To be effective this training must be significantly different to the classroom-based safety training drivers already receive.</P>
                  <P>Objectives:</P>
                  <P>1— to develop and oversee delivery of a highly engaging, innovative and impactful safety training course for bus drivers and bus driver instructors,</P>
                  <P>2— to apply new technology and innovation in delivering this training, enabling drivers to learn from a range of scenarios, including experiencing the road from the perspective of other road users, specifically pedestrians, cyclists and motorcyclists.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
